query-r14.rq.deftemplate: All RDFS Literals of type geo:wktLiteral shall consist of an optional URI identifying the coordinate reference system followed by Simple Features Well Known Text (WKT) describing a geometric value. Valid geo:wktLiterals are formed by concatenating a valid, absolute URI as defined in [RFC 2396], one or more spaces (Unicode U+0020 character) as a separator, and a WKT string as defined in Simple Features [ISO 19125-1].

query-r15.rq.deftemplate: The URI <http://www.opengis.net/def/crs/OGC/1.3/CRS84> shall be assumed as the spatial reference system for geo:wktLiterals that do not specify an explicit spatial reference system URI.

query-r16.rq.deftemplate: Coordinate tuples within geo:wktLiterals shall be interpreted using the axis order defined in the spatial reference system used.

query-r17.rq.deftemplate: An empty RDFS Literal of type geo:wktLiteral shall be interpreted as an empty geometry. Part {{index}} tests {{items}} geometries.

query-r20.rq.deftemplate: All geo:gmlLiterals shall consist of a valid element from the GML schema that implements a subtype of GM_Object as defined in [OGC 07-036].

query-r27.rq.deftemplate: An empty geo:geoJSONLiteral shall be interpreted as an empty geometry. Part {{index}} tests {{items}} geometries.

reqToDescs.query-r14.rq: Requirement 14: All RDFS Literals of type geo:wktLiteral shall consist of an optional IRI identifying the coordinate reference system and a required Well Known Text (WKT) description of a geometric value. Valid geo:wktLiteral instances are formed by either a WKT string as defined in ISO13249 or by concatenating a valid absolute IRI, as defined in [IETF3987], enclosed in angled brackets (< & >) followed by whitespace as a separator, and a WKT string as defined in ISO13249.
reqToDescs.query-r15.rq: Requirement 15: The IRI <http://www.opengis.net/def/crs/OGC/1.3/CRS84> shall be assumed as the spatial reference system for geo:wktLiteral instances that do not specify an explicit spatial reference system IRI
reqToDescs.query-r16.rq: Requirement 16: Coordinate tuples within geo:wktLiteral shall be interpreted using the axis order defined in the spatial reference system used.
reqToDescs.query-r17.rq: Requirement 17: An empty RDFS Literal of type geo:wktLiteral shall be interpreted as an empty Geometry.

reqToDescs.query-r21.rq: Requirement 21: An empty geo:gmlLiteral shall be interpreted as an empty Geometry.

reqToDescs.query-r26.rq: Requirement 26: RDFS Literals of type geo:geoJSONLiteral do not contain a SRS definition. All literals of this type shall, according to the GeoJSON specification, be encoded only in, and be assumed to use, the WGS84 geodetic longitude-latitude spatial reference system (http://www.opengis.net/def/crs/OGC/1.3/CRS84).
reqToDescs.query-r27.rq: Requirement 27: An empty RDFS Literal of type geo:geoJSONLiteral shall be interpreted as an empty Geometry, i.e. {"geometry": null} in GeoJSON .
